# Desktop Environments

Controlled by `desktop` in `variables.nix`. Valid values:

- `"niri"`   — Niri (scrollable-tiling Wayland compositor) + dms-shell bar + GNOME layer
- `"gnome"`  — Full GNOME Shell session (GDM + GNOME Shell + GNOME layer)
- `"cosmic"` — COSMIC DE (System76, long-term exploration)

## Switching

Change one line in `variables.nix`:

    desktop = "gnome";

Then rebuild:

    sudo nixos-rebuild switch

## Structure

| Path             | Purpose                                                         | Loaded by       |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------- |
| `base.nix`       | Common desktop apps (browsers, comms, dev tools, etc.)          | always          |
| `gnome-services.nix`| GNOME services: GDM, keyring, portals, GTK theming, core apps   | niri, gnome     |
| `niri/`          | Niri compositor config                                          | niri            |
| `dms-shell/`     | DankMaterialShell bar/launcher                                  | niri            |
| `gnome/`         | GNOME Shell (imports gnome-services.nix + enables gnome.enable)    | gnome           |
| `cosmic/`        | COSMIC DE                                                       | cosmic          |
